thread.title: Why General Mills Is Paying Up for a Dog’s Breakfast

author: Aaron Back
title: Why General Mills Is Paying Up for a Dog’s Breakfast
text:
It isn’t just humans that are cutting carbs these days, their pets are too.
That is why General Mills, maker of Cinnamon Toast Crunch and Häagen-Dazs, is willing to pay a high price for Blue Buffalo Pet Products, a purveyor of high-protein, natural pet foods.
